last_episode_to_air.name: Undercover No More
last_episode_to_air.overview: The school year comes to an end; the undercover adults reveal their true identities to the students of Highland Park High School and report back to the administrators what they learned about life in high school today.

name: Undercover High
overview: Seven young adults go undercover in Highland Park High School in Topeka, Kansas, in an experiment to provide an inside look into the lives of today's teenagers and the issues they face.

episodes.name: Would You Go Back?
episodes.overview: At Highland Park High School, in Topeka, Kansas, administrators are sending seven adults back to high school to gain unique access and perspectives on the issues teenagers face today.

episodes.name: Race to the Finish
episodes.overview: The first big event of the spring semester gives the undercover adults an opportunity to better understand the school's racially diverse community.

episodes.name: At Risk
episodes.overview: The undercover adults make inroads with at-risk students struggling to beat the odds; two new participants are unsure if they will make any connections at the school.

episodes.name: Shots Fired
episodes.overview: A shooting takes the life of a former student and sends waves through the Highland Park community.

episodes.name: Bullied
episodes.overview: After two months at Highland Park High School, the undercover adults become closer to students battling major life struggles, while a new undercover student named Gloria replaces Kourtnei.

episodes.name: Pregnancy Tests
episodes.overview: The adult participants at Highland Park High School focus on teen pregnancy, sex education, and teen moms.

episodes.name: Stage Fright
episodes.overview: Students and participants stand in the spotlight when Highland Park High School hosts a student-led talent show, but the "Showtime at the Apollo" theme has everyone frightened of getting booed off the stage.

episodes.name: Undercover in Trouble
episodes.overview: In their attempt to uncover the barriers that stand in the way of Highland Park's success, the undercover adults learn that the students they have made connections with are caught in cycles of poverty, crime and troubled home lives.

episodes.name: Busted
episodes.overview: As the end of the school year approaches, students are suspicious of who the participants are, while social media fights circulate throughout the school.

episodes.name: You Only Go to Prom Twice
episodes.overview: With a few weeks left until the end of the semester and the social experiment, the participants help students at Highland Park High School prepare for and go to prom.

episodes.name: Undercover No More
episodes.overview: The school year comes to an end; the undercover adults reveal their true identities to the students of Highland Park High School and report back to the administrators what they learned about life in high school today.
